args.canonical_rel_desc: Indicates that the subject set or collection includes the object as one of its members or examples.
args.justification: Normalize the predicate to a cleaner, more general canonical name ('includes') while the relation class already captures that this is about anatomical structure set membership. The previous name 'includes_structure' redundantly encodes type information that belongs in rel_cls, not in the canonical predicate.
